revision.text:
==English==

{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|consensus|cōnsēnsus|agreement, accordance, unanimity|lang=la}}, from {{term|consentio|cōnsentiō|feel together; agree|lang=la}}; see {{term|consent}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# A process of [[w:Decision making#Decision making in social setting|decision-making]] that seeks widespread agreement among group members.
# [[general#Adjective|General]] agreement among the members of a given group or community, each of which exercises some [[discretion]] in decision-making and follow-up action.
# Average projected value, as in the finance term [[consensus forecast]].

====Related terms====
* [[consensual]]
* [[consent]]

